
[1]abhorrent

   ABHOR'RENT, a.

   1. Hating, detesting, struck with abhorrence.

   2. Contrary, odious, inconsistent with, expressive of extreme
   opposition, as, "Slander is abhorrent to all ideas of justice." In this
   sense, it should be always followed by to - abhorrent from is not
   agreeable to the English idiom.
